                <!-- Weapons -->
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef MayRequire="Rick.FCP.EnergyWeapons">FCP_Gun_Laser_Rifle</thingDef>
                    <count>1</count>
                </li>
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef MayRequire="Rick.FCP.EnergyWeapons">FCP_Gun_Laser_Pistol</thingDef>
                    <count>2</count>
                </li>
                <!-- Starting resources -->
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef>MealSurvivalPack</thingDef>
                    <count>25</count>
                </li>
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef>MedicineIndustrial</thingDef>
                    <count>15</count>
                </li>
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef>ComponentIndustrial</thingDef>
                    <count>25</count>
                </li>
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef>Steel</thingDef>
                    <count>200</count>
                </li>
                <li Class="ScenPart_StartingThing_Defined">
                    <def>StartingThing_Defined</def>
                    <thingDef>Plasteel</thingDef>
                    <count>20</count>
                </li>
                <!-- Game start dialog -->
                <li Class="ScenPart_GameStartDialog">
                    <def>GameStartDialog</def>
                    <text>The Hidden Valley bunker that once sheltered you is now a tomb of metal and failed dreams. Elder Elijah's obsession with the Sierra Madre, the schism with the NCR, years of isolation - it all led to this moment of desperate exodus. You carry what little you could salvage: worn recon armor, a handful of energy weapons, and the bitter knowledge of what the Brotherhood once was. The Mojave sun beats down mercilessly, but it's nothing compared to the weight of rebuilding from ashes. The old ways failed. Perhaps it's time to forge new ones.</text>
